title: clare_(claymore)
body:
The main protagonist of [[Claymore (series)|]].

In the beginning of the series, Clare is the number 47 of [i]The Organization[/i]'s 78th generation, making her the lowest ranked claymore. She also holds the distinction of becoming the first individual to willingly become a claymore (half-human, half-youma female warriors). Her goal is revenge against the awakened being [[priscilla_(claymore)|Priscilla]]. When first introduced, Clare was a very cold warrior who prioritized her duties over everything else, however, she saves [[raki_(claymore)|Raki]] from a youma and takes him under her care because he reminds her of herself when she was younger.

Clare has [[short_hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] with [[bangs]]  and [[grey eyes]]. Her usual outfit consists of [[white bodysuit]], large [[pauldrons]], leather [[vambraces]], [[faulds]] and [[armored boots]]. In the series, Clare is frequently seen wielding a [[claymore_(sword)|]].

title: tio_plato
body:
English: Tio Plato
Japanese: ティオ・プラトー (tio puratou)
Age: 14 ([[zero_no_kiseki|zero]]/[[ao_no_kiseki|ao]]), 16 ([[sen_no_kiseki_iii|sen 3]])

Main character of [[Eiyuu Densetsu]]'s [[zero_no_kiseki|Zero]]/[[Ao no Kiseki]] duology. [[Mishy]] fangirl.

Has an in-game nickname ティオすけ (tiosuke) given her by [[Randolph Orlando]] and adopted by fans. Translated as Tio Tot.

[tn]ティオすけ is a pun on combining ティオ + ちび助. ちび助 (chibisuke, usually written using kana alone) literally means young child, pipsqueak. So meaning of this nickname can be understood as tiny/little Tio.[/tn]
[tn][b]Tio Tot[/b] translation was first introduced by Geofront fan-translation team in [[Zero  no Kiseki]]. Later in [[Sen no Kiseki III]] it was adopted as an official translation.[/tn]
[tn]There is also exists [b]Petiote[/b] variant of translating this nickname, it was found in Guren's fan-translation of [[zero_no_kiseki|Zero]] and [[Ao no Kiseki]]. Petiote is a french slang name for little girl, which is also works as a pun on petite + Tio.[/tn]

h4. See also

* [[Mizuhashi Kaori]], VA

title: geisenborger
body:
Character from [[Granblue Fantasy]]. One of the ten Evokers, pactbearers with unique composite Primal Beasts, Geisenborger himself represents The Chariot among the Major Arcana.

Element: Light
Style: Attack
Age: 34
Height: 205 cm
CV: [[Terasoma Masaki]]

Geisenborger is a [[Draph]] mercenary who lives for the sake of battle. He throws himself into the heart of wars indiscriminately, relishing in battle wherever he goes. A proud warrior in heart and mind, Geisenborger will readily compare any circumstance to a sort of battlefield, even the most mundane things, which often leaves him gravely embarrassed in the aftermath.

[spoiler]During an encounter that left him on the verge of death, a singular prayer caused him to form a pact with [[The Star (Granblue Fantasy)|The Star]], who heard his silent prayer beneath the night skies, and granted him new strength. However, this caused Geisenborger to lose his sense of pain entirely, causing him untold frustration and leaving him despising The Star. Even after his pact is later renewed, under his conditions, he still does not view The Star favorably at all.[/spoiler]

[i]Ima, Koi wo Shiteimasu.[/i] (Now I'm in Love) is a shoujo [[comic|manga]] series written and illustrated by [[Hatta Ayuko]]. title: shouryuuken
body:
The [b]Shouryuuken[/b] (昇龍拳, "Rising Dragon Fist") is a powerful rising [[uppercut]] in the [[Street Fighter]] series that is often used to stop aerial attacks, and as a finisher in the case of the super-move variants, which often have the fist wreathed in Ki or flame.

The Shouryuuken is, along with the [[Hadouken]], the signature move of [[Ryu (street fighter)|Ryu]] and [[Ken Masters|Ken]], and over the course of the series multiple other characters with various degrees of association with them have also been introduced as users of the technique.

h4. Variants

title: pansy
body:
A popular, decorative garden flower hybridized from [i]Viola tricolor[/i] with other [i]Viola[/i] species.  Popular for use in [[flower bed|flower beds]].

Pansies come in practically every color of the rainbow.  Pansies have a very distinctive flower with five petals, arranged with three petals on top, usually with a dark lobe pattern in the center that combines to give the impression of a butterfly.  

This center, darkened pattern is generally how you tell pansies from [[violet_(flower)|violets]] and other [i]Viola[/i] species.

title: jeff_the_killer
body:
One of the earliest and most iconic [[creepypasta]] characters.

The original image of Jeff associated with the story is a photoshopped image of a video still of a middle-aged Asian woman approaching the camera, at which point her face appeared quite white - the photoshop embellished the whiteness of her face further, among other things, becoming the iconic image. It was spread around the Japanese Internet, 2ch in particular, as a surprise/shock image before making its way to the English-speaking Internet. May have some connection to [[Kuchisake-onna]].

In late 2022 and early 2023, as part of the trend of [[AI-generated art (topic)|]] using img2img to create pareidolia-inducing images, several creepypasta images, such as Jeff's, would be inserted to create cute anime girls, to be shared around and cause mental damage to those who look upon them. These AI anime girls in turn have inspired fanart of their own, including those based on [[jeff the killer (ai-gen)|Jeff]].

title: toki_(hokuto_no_ken)
body:
[b]Toki[/b] is the second of the four Hokuto brothers from [[Hokuto no Ken]]. He is a pacifist who seeks to use Hokuto Shinken as a healing art. Toki's self-made technique, Hokuto Ujou Ken (北斗有情拳, "North Star Humane Fist"), is an art that is capable of healing or destroying that which it is used on. When fatally wounded with this style, the dying experiences a great feeling of euphoria, instead of horrifying pain. 

Toki is from the Land of Asura, and along with [[raoh (hokuto no ken)|Raoh]], is orphaned and adopted by Ryuken, who is seeking a student to train. Although he originally doesn't train Toki, Toki shows incredible potential, and he is made to promise that he will stop Raoh if he falls down the wrong path.

During The Nuclear fallout, Toki suffered from radiation after volunteered himself to close the shelter's door (which can only be closed from outside i.e. a plot device), thus limited his power usage, since it will slowly draining his life power out.

h4. Known moves

* 北斗有情破顔拳 ([i][[Hokuto Ujou Hagan Ken]][/i])
** A humane technique where aura blasts fired from the forearms go in two separate directions and make the opponent(s) explode without feeling any pain.

* 北斗有情断迅拳 ([i]Hokuto Ujou Danjin Ken[/i])
** A humane technique that causes multiple opponents' heads to be split without making them feel any pain.

* 闘勁呼法 ([i]Tokei Kohou[/i])
** A secret technique which sends a shockwave through the ground.

* 天翔百裂拳 ([i]Tenshou Hyakuretsu Ken[/i])
** Toki's airborne version of the [i]Hokuto Hyakuretsu Ken[/i].

title: nissan_sileighty
body:
Also spelled as "Sil-80," it is a popular modification for the [[Nissan 180SX]] that refits it with the front end of a [[Nissan Silvia]], therefore having the front of a [b]Sil[/b]via and the rear of a 1[b]80[/b]SX. The inverse (S13 with 180SX front end) exists as the less-popular [[Nissan Onevia]].

500 officially licensed Sileighties were built by Japanese tuning company Kid's Heart. Unofficial Sileighties were usually created to repair damaged 180SX models since new Silvia front-ends were cheaper than the 180SX's, likely due to their lack of pop-up headlights. 

The Sileighty is most notable for it's appearance in [[Initial D]], where it is driven by [[Satou Mako]] and her navigator [[Sayuki (initial d)|]].

title: mahjong_tile
body:
A thick, blocky tile used in the game of [[mahjong]]. Mahjong tiles are traditionally made of bamboo and bone, although most modern tiles are made of plastic.

A mahjong set usually consists of 144 tiles. They are:
* 108 suited tiles. There are three suits, each numbered 1 to 9 with four tiles each number, thus 36 per suit:
** Circles
** Bamboos (1 Bamboo actually has a bird pictured to deter cheating by adding more bamboo lines)
** Characters (Chinese numerals with 萬, [i]man[/i]/[i]wan[/i] written on the lower part)
* 28 honor tiles that are suitless:
** 16 Wind tiles, four each for North (北), South (南), East (東), and West (西).
** 12 Dragon tiles, with four tiles for each "color":
*** Red Dragon, symbolized by a red 中
*** Green Dragon, symbolized by a green 發
*** White Dragon, which is blank in Japanese sets (Some other sets have White Dragon tiles with a decorative blue rectangle on each to distinguish them from replacement tiles.)
* 8 optional "flower" tiles, so called because they are often depicted with flowers (many sets have them, but some including Japanese sets don't):
** 4 tiles representing actual flowers: plum (梅), orchid (蘭), chrysanthemum (菊), and bamboo (竹)
** 4 tiles representing seasons: spring (春), summer (夏), autumn (秋), and winter (冬)

title: tetsuwan_birdy
body:
Also known as [b]Birdy the Mighty[/b], it is a manga series by [[Yuuki Masami]] initially made from 1985 to 1988. A reboot was produced that ran from 2002 until 2008. A four-episode OAV was also made in 1996, followed by a 25-episode anime from July 2008 to March 2009.

[[Birdy Cephon Altera]] is a Federation agent chasing interplanetary criminals to the planet Earth. While in pursuit of one such criminal, she accidentally kills a high school boy named [[Senkawa Tsutomu]]. However, there is a way to keep him alive. He ends up being merged into Birdy's body and must remain so until the repair of his body is complete. Tsutomu is stuck sharing a body with an attractive, strong, and impulsive space police agent while trying to keep his family and friends from finding out about Birdy. In the meantime, Birdy continues her investigation. Together, they take on a secretive group of evil aliens planning to perform experiments on the unsuspecting inhabitants of Earth.

He is a [[rabbit boy|rabbit]] [[furry male|boy]] with [[red eyes]] and [[white fur]]. He wears a full [[suit]] comprising of a [[black headwear|black]] [[top hat]], a [[black coat]] with [[long sleeves]], a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt]] with [[center frills]] and a [[black bowtie]], [[black pants]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]].

title: kanaria
body:
[i]Canary Bird[/i]

Second of the [[Rozen Maiden]] dolls. She claims to be the smartest of the dolls, but her plans to steal the others' Rosa Mysticae usually end in comedy. She battles with her [[violin]]. Her master is [[Kusabue Mitsu]]. She has the unusual habit of ending her sentences with "kashira" ("I wonder?" or "maybe?"), which is likened to [[Hinaichigo]]'s penchant for ending sentences with "na no" (meaning "Because"). 

She has [[green eyes]] and [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[green hair]] with an [[ahoge]], [[twin drills]], and [[swept bangs]] adorned with a [[heart hair ornament]] and a [[red rose]]. Her [[lolita fashion|outfit]] consists of a [[square neckline|square-necklined]] [[lace-trimmed coat|lace-trimmed]] [[yellow coat]] with [[frilled sleeves|frilled]] [[juliet sleeves]] with [[yellow ribbon|yellow]] [[sleeve ribbon]]s and a [[brown ribbon|brown]] [[neck ribbon]] over an [[orange romper]], [[white pantyhose]], and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[mary janes]]. She usually carries her [[orange umbrella|orange]] [[parasol]] wherever she goes.

She has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] with [[medium bangs]] and [[brown eyes]]. Her [[school uniform]] varies, but it is usually a [[serafuku]] with a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[yellow jacket]], a [[white shirt]], a [[blue sailor collar]] with a [[pink necktie]], and a [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[black skirt]]. She also frequently carries her [[weapon bag]] for her [[shinai]].

title: yamada-san
body:
A net character, outside the core circle of [[OS-tan|OS-tans]].

Her history is as follows: The Windows logo turned on the side looks a lot like the very common Japanese family name "Yamada" written vertically:

山
田

She was an early suggestion for a design for Windows 98, but never caught on because she was too plain. Nowadays she's mostly given up on being an OS and lives with [[we-tan|WE-tan]] (who still wants to be one), [[Astaroth (Shinrabanshou)|Astaroth]], and [[Spider-man|Spidey]]. She works as an [[office_lady|OL]], and has no distinguishing characteristics whatsoever. She's from Niigata, the most boring Japanese perfecture. She likes staying up late and watching TV.

She works at the same office as [[we-tan|WE-tan/Taeko-san]], [[2k-kun|2k-kun]], [[eigyouseki|Eigyouseki]] (the businessman mutation of the super-deformed [[suiseiseki|Suiseiseki]]), and a grown-up [[hinaichigo|Hina Ichigo]] who's name I don't really know. Their boss is [[darth_vader|Darth Vader]], who writes his name "米田さん", or "Beida-san".

title: diffraction_spikes
body:
Diffraction spikes manifest as multiple spikes radiating from a point of light, similar to a [[lens flare]] which manifests as overall haziness and artifacts in the image.

[[Sparkle]], [[glint]], and [b]diffraction spikes[/b] all refer to similar patterns of bright lines radiating from a point. They are not clearly differentiated, and usage tends to be context-sensitive. In general:
* [[Sparkle]] is considered the base case. Usually four lines at right angles radiating from a point. Associated with eyes, liquid or particulate matter (e.g. raindrops, snow, sand), or nothing (appearing mid-air). Can appear in large numbers.
* [[Glint]] is associated with solid objects, especially ones which are metallic and/or sharp. Usually appear singly or in small numbers.
* [b]Diffraction spikes[/b] is the technical term for the phenomenon in general, but is used less often. Can be used for more realistic-looking effects or conversely when appearing extremely large and exaggerated. More likely than sparkle and glint to be asymmetric or to have more than four radiating lines.

h4. See also

* [[lens flare]]
* [[bokeh]]
* [[light particles]]
* [[Tag group:Image Composition]]

h4. External Links

* "Wikipedia: Diffraction Spikes":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diffraction_spike]

title: hazmat_suit
body:
A hazmat suit (hazardous material suit) is a full body protective suit designed to protect the user from chemical, biological, nuclear or radiological hazards.

Most of them cover from head to toes and some are completely airtight.

They can be used with a [[gas mask]] to filter external air. Those with "positive pressure" (to guard against any fissure of the suit) have a balloon-like appearance.

May be seen at use during acts of [[terrorism]], plagues, the [[apocalypse]] or [[post-apocalypse]] scenarios. Their users might be doctors or members of public forces.

title: shining_shoot_(pose)
body:
Iconic pose from the opening of [i][[gundam_08th_ms_team|Mobile Suit Gundam: 08th MS Team]][/i]. It features an [[ground_gundam|RX-79G Gundam Ground Type]] firing a 180mm cannon, with a discarded shield in the foreground. The pose name derives from the shooting of the weapon, and the accompanying theme song [i]Arashi no Nakade de Kagayaite[/i] (嵐の中で輝いて, lit. 'Shining in the Storm').

Due to the angle and perspective, an optical illusion causes the barrel of the cannon to look to be balanced atop the upper rail of the shield. The comparative size of the shield to other appearances, and the brief motion of the barrel behind the rail disprove the effect on closer examination. Nevertheless, the perceived pose became so popular that was later replicated via effect parts in certain official merchandise.

A [[Kantai Collection]] meme character. A fanmade variation of [[Inazuma (kancolle)|]] that became meme enough to become a trend among Pixiv artists. She in originated in post #1917287 by [[Sukima (crie)|]].

She appears generally identical to Inazuma, but often a [[chibi]] figure (or deformed in a muscle-bound manner), and classically has a [[diamond mouth]] face with eyes that are [[solid_circle_eyes|large solid black circles]], upturned eyebrows, [[shaded_face|shading on her face]], and the oddly-shaped mouth twisted into a trolling smirk (see post #1680938). Frequently, she can be made to appear thuggish instead of smirking.  Plasma-chan is also a highly violent "dark-side" version of Inazuma, usually threatening people (or eggplants) with weapons or martial arts (see post #1726517). Alternately, simply behaving in a manner deliberately the opposite of the "pure and innocent" normal Inazuma (see post #1703511).

Plasma-chan was, in the Twitter images that originated her meme, violently opposed to an artist named [[Nasu (tenpurakkusu)|]] (Japanese for "[[eggplant]]") and featured the [[solid circle eyes]] and [[diamond mouth]] face as her salient traits in the series.  Some references to Plasma-chan just have her head and a "nasu" speech bubble. 

Inazuma's name means "lightning" in Japanese, so she becomes "plasma" as her dark side. 

Inazuma's catchphrase "[[nanodesu_(phrase)|]]" (なのです) may be [i]just slightly[/i] altered into "な゛の゛て゛す! (nano-DEATH!)" instead (alternately, "なの-DEATH!").

title: girls'_frontline_glitch_land
body:
A fan game-turned-official announced during MICA Team's 4th Anniversary Stream, May 15, 2020. A top-down side scrolling pixel-based adventure game set to star [[HK416 (girls' frontline)|]] as the main protagonist, set before the beginning of the core [[Girls' Frontline]] story. Other characters that were slated to appear, aside those original to it (i.e. Anna, a SF researcher, and unnamed characters from its teaser), included [[Thunder (girls' frontline)|]] (wearing a labcoat) and [[M870 (girls' frontline)|]].

Was announced to be "shelved":https://www.reddit.com/r/girlsfrontline/comments/spz4e3/news_on_gfl_glitchland/ on February 11, 2021, a victim of increasing regulations on game registration in China (including the suspension of the approval of newly registered gaming IPs) preventing the game's release, with the original creator leaving Sunborn amicably and speaking favorably of his time there.

title: hakka_no_togame_(bankai)
body: Bankai: Hakka no Togame (白霞罸, Censure of the White Haze; Viz "White Haze Punishment"): Rukia's Bankai changes both her physical look and the clothing she is wearing dramatically. Rukia wears a white, ankle-length kimono with lined patterns. The robe has an attached ornate collar, edges, and shoulder design with long, wide sleeves. There are long, flowing ribbons tied at her back that form numerous large loops. She has a small ice flower formation at the center of her chest, and a half crown of ice which extends around the back of her head. Rukia's hair becomes white, and her blade becomes transparent ice.
